    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-02T11:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-02T11:25:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">662A.00/9–254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d10fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_LYONCB1"
                            >Lyon</persName> and cleared with <gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>,
                            <gloss target="#t_RA1">RA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>,
                        and <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>; repeated to London and Bonn.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-02T12:25:00-04:00"
                            >September 2, 1954—12:25 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>804. Confirming <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName>’s
                    telephone conversation with <persName corresp="#p_DILLONCD1">Dillon</persName>
                    we have informed British here of <persName corresp="#p_DOWLINGWC1"
                        >Dowling</persName>’s telephonic report to <persName
                        corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> to effect that <persName
                        corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName>’s reaction to Protocols was more
                    violently negative than anticipated<note n="2" xml:id="d10fn2">For a summary of
                            <persName corresp="#p_CONANTJB1">Conant</persName>’s conversation with
                        Chancellor <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> concerning
                        the protocols, see telegram 663 from Bonn, Sept. 2, <ref target="#pg_1138"
                            >p. 1138</ref>.</note> and recommending postponement <hi rend="italic"
                        >démarche</hi> to <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFP1">Mendes-France</persName>.
                    British informed us they are telephoning and cabling London at once as follows: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>At our request interview scheduled with <persName
                                corresp="#p_MENDESFP1">Mendes-France</persName> this afternoon be
                            postponed until we all have an opportunity know results (<hi
                                rend="italic">a</hi>) <persName corresp="#p_CONANTJB1"
                                >Conant</persName>’s and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) <persName>Hover
                                Millar</persName>’s interviews with <persName
                                corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName>.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>That we are instructing Amb. <persName corresp="#p_DILLONCD1"
                                >Dillon</persName> not to accompany <persName corresp="#p_JEBBSGHM1"
                                >Jebb</persName> to interview with <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFP1"
                                >Mendes-France</persName> this evening even if British insist upon
                            going through with it.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>We emphasized to British our feeling that purpose Protocol operation was to
                    assist <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName> and that his views
                    as expressed to <persName corresp="#p_CONANTJB1">Conant</persName> indicated
                    that far from being helpful it might prove harmful to him. British underlined to
                    us their fear that if there were not a joint <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi>,
                    element of US–UK solidarity which is so necessary in coming weeks would be
                    lacking. They appreciated however grave risk Protocols leaking to press once
                    they are in French hands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
